channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Buyer's Remorse: Almost Half of US EV Owners Want to Switch Back to Good Ol' Internal Combustion Engines
Biden, Trump face off at CNN Presidential Debate which may 'change the narrative in a massive way'
item.description: There's an incredible amount at stake in Thursday's first debate between President Biden and former President Trump, as the face off on the same stage in battleground Georgia

item.title: IRS Delays Identity Theft Cases, Watchdog Reports
item.description: The IRS is taking nearly two years to resolve identity theft cases, causing significant delays for affected taxpayers, according to a recent report from the National Taxpayer Advocate.

item.title: CNN Host Snipes at GOP Rep: ‘What Does This Have to Do With Joe Biden? Let’s Talk About Donald Trump!’
Trump-era China sanctions ended by Biden may be revived under new House GOP bill
item.description: A group of House Republican lawmakers is introducing legislation to undo the Biden administration's reversal of Trump administration-era sanctions against a CCP entity.

item.title: Speaker Johnson Supports La. Ten Commandments Law
item.description: House Speaker Mike Johnson, R-La., said he is in favor of a new law in his home state that requires the Ten Commandments be placed in every public school classroom.

item.title: Deep State Exposed: New Congressional Report Shows All the Players Colluding for the 2020 Election
Judge rules Montana law defining sex as only male or female is unconstitutional
item.description: A judge ruled that a Montana law that defined "sex" in state law as only male or female was unconstitutional, following a legal challenge against the law.

item.title: Rep. Ogles to Newsmax: World More Dangerous Due to Biden
item.description: Rep. Andy Ogles, R- Tenn., told Newsmax Wednesday that President Joe Biden's border and foreign policies have made the country and the world more dangerous.

item.title: WATCH: Tucker Carlson Delivers an Absolute Masterclass in How to Deal With a Dishonest Reporter
Republicans plan to slam latest Biden union assist in Thursday oversight hearing
item.description: A subcommittee of the House Oversight Committee will examine the Project Labor Agreements For Federal Construction Projects mandate from the White House on Thursday.

item.title: Karoline Leavitt to Newsmax: Hope Debate Moderators Can Be Fair
item.description: If the debate moderators can be fair, Donald Trump has a "great opportunity" to "highlight his strength versus Joe Biden's weakness, and to contrast his record of success with Joe Biden's record of abysmal failures," Trump campaign spokeswoman Karoline Leavitt said.

item.title: Border Crossings Have Dropped, But at What Cost?
Biden unveils GOP endorsement, Trump reaches out to historically Dem voting bloc: 'Against the grain'
item.description: The Biden and Trump presidential campaigns — on the eve of the first debate — reach out to key constituencies in an attempt to gain an advantage in what may end up being a photo finish.

item.title: Dems Try Forcing Vote on 'Red Flag' Gun Bill
item.description: House Democrats announced a plan on Wednesday to circumvent GOP leadership and force a vote on "red flag" gun laws, according to Axios.
